 Port Elizabeth - During the early hours of Tuesday morning, at about  00:30, while police officers of the Public Order Policing (POP) Unit were busy with stop and search operations in Daku Street in Kwazakele, they heard the sound of a gunshot. "Soon after that, they spotted a maroon Suzuki Celerio with five occupants. The vehicle was stopped and searched," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "A CZ 9mm pistol (serial number filed off) and five rounds of ammunition was found in the vehicle. "All five occupants (3 males and 2 females), aged between 21 and 28 were arrested and detained on a charge of prohibited possession of a firearm, illegal possession of ammunition and discharging of firearm in a built up area. "The vehicle was also impounded for further investigation." She said that the suspects are expected to appear in the Motherwell Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday. "The firearm will be sent to ballistics for analysis."  In another unrelated incident, it is alleged that on Monday, at about 21: 15, Public Order Policing members searched a house in Mdani Street in Zwide after receiving information about drugs at the house. "A total of 75 dagga cigarettes, 3 clear plastic bags containing tik weighing 15 grams, 7 envelopes containing dagga and 2 plastic bags containing loose dagga were confiscated.  The total estimated value of the drugs is R10 000," Col Naidu said. "A 38-year-old man was arrested and will appear in court on Wednesday on a charge of dealing in drugs." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 